# PostPilot API

## Stack

NestJS modular monolith · Prisma 7 · PostgreSQL · `@prisma/adapter-pg` · cookie auth · Zod validation

## Pattern

Controller → Service → Prisma. Controllers thin; business logic in services.

## Structure

- `api/src/<domain>/` — module, controller, service (auth, posts, channels, telegram, bot-connections)
- Prisma only via `PrismaService` (global module)
- DTOs / Zod schemas for request validation

## Prisma 7

- `schema.prisma`: `moduleFormat = "cjs"`, output `../src/generated/prisma`
- Import: `from '../generated/prisma/client'` (not `@prisma/client`)
- Migrations: `prisma migrate dev` locally, `migrate deploy` on staging/prod
- Schema is source of truth; do not edit DB manually

## API conventions

- Global prefix: `/api` (health → `/api/health`)
- Global `AuthGuard`; use `@Public()` for open routes
- Secrets only in `api/.env`; `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` never on frontend
- Errors without stack trace leakage to client
- HttpOnly session cookies; bcrypt for passwords

## Modules

| Module | Routes |
|--------|--------|
| Health | `GET /api/health` |
| Auth | `/api/auth/*` |
| Posts | `/api/posts/*` incl. publish |
| Channels | `/api/channels/*` |
| Bot | `/api/bot/*` |

## Testing

Unit tests in `*.spec.ts` for critical business logic (auth, publish, crypto).
E2E in `api/test/`. See `.cursor/rules/tests.mdc`.
